{
  "texts": [
    "Several recent studies have proposed the use of the convolutional layer to capture local contexts from large sequences of essays (Taghipour and Ng 2016; Hussein et al. 2020; Dong and Zhang 2016; Dong et al. 2017; Liang et al. 2018; Ridley et al. 2020 Ridley et al., 2021)).",
    "A convolution for segment (window), x in an essay, Conv(x), is computed as follows:",
    "where W is the filter, b the bias and x is an input window.",
    "The window slides across the essay, collecting all the feature maps that can ultimately be utilized for score prediction.",
    "Recurrent neural networks (RNNs) are a type of neural network specifically designed for processing sequential data."
  ]
}